subject: DataStructures
question: What is a Set structure?
answer:
It is a pile of data elements which cannot have repeated elements, and items are not in a particular order. It is used just for checking the presence of an item.
And the methods to manipulate it are:
has returning if any given value exists,
values that returns the entires collection,
add to add an item that does not exist,
remove an existing element,
size to know the number if elements,
union that combines 2 sets to create a new one,
intersection that combines repeated elements of 2 sets and creates a new set,
difference creates a news set with the elements of the first set that are not on the second set,
and subset, that returns true if the first set exists completely on the second set.
